科目名稱 :
英語語言學概論(一)











INTRODUCTION TO LINGUISTICS 
       "Linguistics is the science of language. It is the subject whose
practitioners devote their energy to understanding why human language is the
way it is. They study the history, acquisition, structure, and use of as many languages
as possible --- It would be nice to study them all, but life's too short."
--- (Crystal: http://www.bangor.ac.uk/ling/whatis.htm) 
 




部別 : 進修學院二技


100學年度第1學期


:November 19, 2011




 







科目名稱 : 英語語言學概論


開課班級 : 進修學院外三甲


學　　分 : 2.0


授課時數 : 2.0




授課教師 : 黃士人


 


 


 










1.教學目標




Linguistics
    is usually defined as the scientific study of language. The aim of this
    course is to provide students with a general understanding of linguistics.
    It will cover major fields in linguistics, such as syntax, phonetics,
    phonology, semantics, morphology, language acquisition, sociolinguistics,
    etc. At the end of the semester, students are expected to master major
    concepts and tools in linguistics and be able to use them in analyzing and
    understanding languages. 










2.教學綱要




1.
    Phonetics 2. Phonology 3. Morphology 4. Syntax 5. Semantics 










3.教科書



 



1


書名 : Language Files (10th ed)　出版日期 : 年 月 




作者 : Bergmann, Anouschka
    et al.　出版社 : The Ohio State University　版本 : 











4.參考書



 



1


書名 : An Introduction to Language (7th ed)　出版日期 : 年 月 




作者 : Fromkin,
    Victoria and Robert Rodman　出版社 : Harcout
    Brace College Publishers　　版本 : 











